Use of the appendix to replace the choledochus. Ten cases of choledochal cyst (CC) were treated by biliary-appendicoduodenostomy. The follow-up comprised a patient interview, ultrasonography (US), and single-proton ejected computerized tomography (SPECT) scanning. In all cases an anti-reflux submucosal tunnel was added to the distal appendico-duodenostomy all showed an uneventful postoperative course. All the dilated intrahepatic bile ducts had normalized on B-US postoperatively. Four children under went SPECT examination